Package ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.plugin.types

Class Imyhat

java.lang.Object
ca.on.oicr.gsi.shesmu.plugin.types.Imyhat
Direct Known Subclasses:
Imyhat.AlgebraicImyhat, Imyhat.BaseImyhat, Imyhat.DictionaryImyhat, Imyhat.ListImyhat, Imyhat.ObjectImyhat, Imyhat.OptionalImyhat, Imyhat.TupleImyhat
public abstract class Imyhat extends Object
Types as represented in Shesmu

This word means “which/pattern of conduct” in ancient Egyptian to avoid naming conflicts with other classes named type.

Java's Class are unsuitable for this purpose because generic erasure has happened. Shesmu types also have an interchange string format, called a descriptor.
